VERSION 2.0.0 - current
=============

2019-03-03  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * usage of various third-party tools like Codacy (code quality), and CII Best Practices

2019-02-23  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * usage of shellcheck to improve efficiency, robustness and compatibility

2019-02-14  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * extraction from Hemera project to a new dedicated one

VERSION 0.1.5
=============

2011-07-24  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * improved daemon process management

2011-06-12  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * implemented new version of message management system (info, message, warning, error)

2011-06-11  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * improved variables management (initialization is mandatory, and read-only variables/constants are defined as that).

 * implemented powerful system allowing to "dump" function call stack in case of error (excluding some well known exit status), or when a script exits with an exit status different from 0

 * improved log file management (no more double messages), and fixed some incomplete log files

2011-05-29  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * added check on OS locale feature (must use UTF-8 charmaps, and it must be installed)

2011-05-18  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * implemented powerful path management for PATH and LD_LIBRARY_PATH update (including support of '*' wilcard)

2011-05-16  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * implemented version system (giving precise information if source code version)

 * configuration file is now lookup in $HOME/.xxx by default, allowing any user to have specific configuration

2011-05-11  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * implemented uptime functions

VERSION 0.1.1
=============

2011-07-27  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * improved path management in some extrems situation (under Debian-like GNU/Linux distribution, when user launch script without having installed GNU version of 'which')

VERSION 0.1.0
=============

2011-04-08  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * released version 0.1

2010-10-15  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * improved system allowing to kill child processes (no more "broken pipe")

2010-10-14  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * improved some global variables management (did not reset anymore if already set)

2010-10-01  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * formalized error code status (constants definition, and use everywhere)

2010-09-27  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * improved process/pid system

 * implemented a system allowing to kill child processes when daemon is stopped

2010-09-23  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * implemented a process/pid system allowing to start/status/stop daemon

 * various improvements (functions updating environment, new configuration elements, new global variable)

2010-08-12  Bertrand Benoit <contact@bertrand-benoit.net>

 * created main project
